       [-trim_antenna_back_to_shape]

       [-trim_antenna_max_distance]

       [-trim_stripe]

       [-use_exact_spacing]

       [-use_point2point_router]

       [-use_stripe_width]

       [-via_using_exact_crossover_size]

       [-quiet]

       [-nonDefault]

       Returns the current settings of the setAddStripeMode command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each getAddStripeMode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man getAddStripeMode

       -parameter_names
              Returns  information for the specified parameters. You can spec-
              ify one or more parameters.

              See setAddStripeMode for descriptions  of  the  setAddStripeMode
              parameters you can specify.

       -quiet Returns the current settings for the specified parameters in Tcl
              list  format only. If you specify -quiet without any parameters,
              the  software  returns  the  current   settings   of   all   se-
              tAddStripeMode parameters in Tcl list format.

Examples
              * The  following  command  returns  the  current settings of se-
                tAddStripeMode -offset_from_core in the Tcl list format:

                setAddStripeMode -offset_from_core -quiet

                The software returns the following information:

                true

              * The following command returns the  current  settings  for  se-
                tAddStripeMode -offset_from_core:

                setAddStripeMode -offset_from_core

                The software returns the following information:

                -offset_from_core true # bool, default=true

